text: Hoeksche Waard is a municipality in the Dutch province of South Holland. In 2019, 86,732 people lived there. It was created on 1 January 2019 from the former municipalities of Binnenmaas, Cromstrijen, Korendijk, Oud-Beijerland, and Strijen. Category:2019 establishments in the Netherlands
title: Hoeksche Waard
